spanGrp.span: Se se se keglö-wa të óshkoro te-gẽ-wã
jekepa í të diglö bal mẽ-gẽ-ka
and put the chicken in it.
je nã í të óshkoro jiejawẽ-gẽ-mĩ
Next they pluck off all the feathers.
despues í të todo í köyögö ye tule-gẽ-mĩ
After plucking it, they burn it and then they chop it up.
Kwando köyögö yatula-mĩ-ite ka í (_) paglöwẽ-gẽ-nẽ-ite paglöwẽ-gẽ-nẽ-ite ska ra í wötie-gẽ-nẽ-ite
Jeska í ñã' ye-gẽ-sã'-ite í ñã'
and throw them away together with its fat.
je begemẽnẽwẽ-gẽũ-mĩ-ite jela jirö ol kwãwãlë ĩã nẽ
They then cut the meat into pieces
jekepa í todo je í yaka wötie-gẽ-ite wötie-gẽ-ite
and put it into a pot
Then the owners sit down and eat it.’
Jeska/ í tö (r)/ tögapa í wakwa ñã jöglö-gẽ-wã-nẽ yökö
